If all the checks pass, the function calculates the sum of the numbers and the count of numbers, and returns the average by dividing the sum by the count.

The time complexity of this function is O(n), where n is the length of the input list, because it iterates over each element once. The space complexity is O(1) because it only uses a constant amount of extra space to store the total and count variables.

